Switch the VoltDB integration to use the native [VoltDB Python client](https://pypi.org/project/voltdbclient/) instead of the deprecated HTTP/JSON interface. Instance configuration now takes `host` and `port` (default `21212`) instead of `url`, and TLS is configured through `use_ssl` and `ssl_config_file`. The legacy `url` option is still accepted for backwards compatibility — the host is extracted from the URL and the default native client port is used, with a deprecation warning. Statistics columns are now looked up by name so the check tolerates VoltDB releases that add or drop columns.
